/jekyll/2024-07-12-quantum_computing.htm.title: Quantum Computing
/jekyll/2024-07-12-quantum_computing.htm.body: Quantum information systems are built up of four components: State Dynamics Measurement Observables States are made up of qubits which are complex vectors in a hilbert space $\mathcal{H}$ which is just a vector space equiped with an inner product.
